{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b5de381f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "title: \"Stimulating the brain\"\n",
    "subtitle: \"Driving a neural-mass model with an Event\"\n",
    "format:\n",
    "  html:\n",
    "    code-fold: false\n",
    "    toc: true\n",
    "    echo: true\n",
    "    embed-resources: true\n",
    "    fig-width: 8\n",
    "    out-width: \"100%\"\n",
    "jupyter: python3\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Goal\n",
    "\n",
    "Use a TVB-O `SimulationExperiment` with a stimulus defined as an `Event`. Compare the resting and stimulated time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "46650100",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from tvbo import Dynamics, SimulationExperiment\n",
    "from tvbo.datamodel.schema import Event"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "781d4d26",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. A baseline experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "Start with the `Generic2dOscillator` (G2D) and its database defaults. The trajectory relaxes onto a stable focus at `V ≈ −0.19`. These parameters are **far from any oscillation**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "ea275a5a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "STEP 1: Running simulation...\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Simulation period: 1000.0 ms, dt: 0.01220703125 ms\n",
      "  Transient period: 0.0 ms\n",
      "  Simulation complete.\n",
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "Experiment complete.\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2160x1500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "g2d = Dynamics.from_db(\"Generic2dOscillator\")\n",
    "\n",
    "exp = SimulationExperiment(dynamics=g2d)\n",
    "res = exp.run()\n",
    "res.integration.sel(variable=\"V\").plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0bc5686e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Define a stimulus as an `Event`\n",
    "\n",
    "An `Event` is a symbolic, time-dependent perturbation. Here, a rectangular pulse is defined using `Piecewise`. Any expression in `t` and the event's parameters is valid."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "c0344bd3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "event = Event(\n",
    "    name=\"perturbation\",\n",
    "    event_type=\"stimulus\",\n",
    "    parameters={\n",
    "        \"onset\":     {\"value\": 200.0},\n",
    "        \"width\":     {\"value\": 200.0},\n",
    "        \"amplitude\": {\"value\": 1.0},\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    equation={\n",
    "        \"rhs\": \"Piecewise((amplitude, (t >= onset) & (t < onset + width)), (0.0, True))\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    ")\n",
    "event.plot();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d0f4e65e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "The default G2D enters the oscillatory regime at `I ≈ 3.7` (lower Hopf). At `I + perturbation = 5`, the system is **above** the Hopf, so a limit cycle appears during the pulse.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3. Inject the event into the model\n",
    "\n",
    "Steps:\n",
    "1. Register the event under `exp.events[\"<name>\"]`.\n",
    "2. Edit the right-hand side of the state variable to be driven. Here, for `V`, replace the constant input `I` with `(I + perturbation)`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "5c968ec5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "exp.events[\"perturbation\"] = event\n",
    "exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"V\"].equation.rhs = (\n",
    "    \"d*tau*((I + perturbation)*gamma - V**3*f + V**2*e + V*g \"\n",
    "    \"+ V*local_coupling + W*alpha + c_glob*gamma)\"\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "04793383",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "## Widen the `W` domain before running\n",
    "\n",
    "G2D uses `W ∈ [−6, 6]` as its state-variable domain. The JAX kernel wraps `Heun` in a `BoundedSolver` that clamps `W` at those limits. At `I = 5`, the limit cycle swings `W` down to about `−9`, so the solver pins `W` at `−6`. `V` then settles on the cubic's right branch at `V ≈ 2.88`, a square plateau rather than an oscillation. Widen the domain before running.\n",
    ":::"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "b649f2ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "STEP 1: Running simulation...\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Simulation period: 1000.0 ms, dt: 0.01220703125 ms\n",
      "  Transient period: 0.0 ms\n",
      "  Simulation complete.\n",
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "Experiment complete.\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Axes: xlabel='t', ylabel='perturbation'>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2160x1500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"W\"].domain.lo = -20.0\n",
    "exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"W\"].domain.hi = 20.0\n",
    "\n",
    "res_stim = exp.run()\n",
    "res_stim.integration.sel(variable=\"V\").plot(ax=ax)\n",
    "ax2=ax.twinx()\n",
    "event.plot(ax=ax2, alpha=0.5, linestyle=':')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a4105661",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now the trajectory oscillates during the pulse and returns to the stable focus after.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. Five-node motif: stimulus propagation\n",
    "\n",
    "The five-region motif below uses the same parameter regime as the Bayesian workshop example. The stimulus is brief, so R0 gives one evoked response rather than a long driven oscillation. Edge weights and tract lengths live in edge parameters.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "    R0 -> R1 -> R2\n",
    "          |\n",
    "          v\n",
    "          R3 -> R4\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "R0 is the stimulated site (peripheral). R1 is a hub (degree 3) with high excitability. R3 is also hyperexcitable. R2 and R4 are quiet leaves.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "## Coupling gain\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `a = 0.1`, matching the workshop example. The node excitabilities are `I = [0.05, 0.30, 0.05, 0.25, 0.05]`: R1 and R3 are hot, R0, R2, and R4 are quiet.\n",
    ":::"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "3d640ad2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 3000x3000 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from tvbo import Network, SimulationExperiment, Dynamics, Coupling\n",
    "from tvbo.datamodel.schema import Event\n",
    "\n",
    "T1 = 150.0\n",
    "DT = 0.2\n",
    "ONSET = 10.0\n",
    "DURATION = 1.0\n",
    "G_COUPLING = 0.1\n",
    "TRUE_AMPLITUDE = 0.4\n",
    "DYNAMICS_PARAMS = {\n",
    "    \"a\": -1.5,\n",
    "    \"b\": -15.0,\n",
    "    \"c\": 0.0,\n",
    "    \"d\": 0.015,\n",
    "    \"e\": 3.0,\n",
    "    \"f\": 1.0,\n",
    "    \"tau\": 4.0,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "network_yaml = \"\"\"\n",
    "label: StimPropagationMotif\n",
    "number_of_nodes: 5\n",
    "nodes:\n",
    "    - {id: 0, label: R0, description: \"stimulated site, peripheral, quiet\", parameters: {I: {value: 0.05}}}\n",
    "    - {id: 1, label: R1, description: \"hub, hyperexcitable\", parameters: {I: {value: 0.30}}}\n",
    "    - {id: 2, label: R2, description: \"quiet leaf\", parameters: {I: {value: 0.05}}}\n",
    "    - {id: 3, label: R3, description: \"hyperexcitable branch node\", parameters: {I: {value: 0.25}}}\n",
    "    - {id: 4, label: R4, description: \"quiet leaf\", parameters: {I: {value: 0.05}}}\n",
    "edges:\n",
    "    - {source: 0, target: 1, directed: true, parameters: {weight: {value: .1}, length: {value: 30.0, unit: mm}}}\n",
    "    - {source: 0, target: 3, directed: true, parameters: {weight: {value: .1}, length: {value: 100.0, unit: mm}}}\n",
    "    - {source: 3, target: 4, directed: true, parameters: {weight: {value: .1}, length: {value: 30.0, unit: mm}}}\n",
    "    - {source: 1, target: 2, directed: true, parameters: {weight: {value: .1}, length: {value: 30.0, unit: mm}}}\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "network = Network.from_string(network_yaml)\n",
    "\n",
    "network.plot_overview()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "9664a86f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "STEP 1: Running simulation...\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Simulation period: 150.0 ms, dt: 0.2 ms\n",
      "  Transient period: 0.0 ms\n",
      "  Simulation complete.\n",
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "Experiment complete.\n",
      "============================================================\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "event = Event(\n",
    "    name=\"perturbation\",\n",
    "    event_type=\"stimulus\",\n",
    "    parameters={\n",
    "        \"onset\": {\"value\": ONSET},\n",
    "        \"duration\": {\"value\": DURATION},\n",
    "        \"amplitude\": {\"value\": TRUE_AMPLITUDE},\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    equation={\"rhs\": \"Piecewise((amplitude, (t >= onset) & (t < onset + duration)), (0.0, True))\"},\n",
    "    regions=[0],\n",
    "    weighting=[1.0],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "dynamics = Dynamics.from_db(\"Generic2dOscillator\")\n",
    "for name, value in DYNAMICS_PARAMS.items():\n",
    "    dynamics.parameters[name].value = value\n",
    "\n",
    "exp = SimulationExperiment(\n",
    "    dynamics=dynamics,\n",
    "    coupling=Coupling(name=\"Linear\", parameters={\"a\": {\"value\": G_COUPLING}, \"b\": {\"value\": 0.0}}),\n",
    "    network=network,\n",
    ")\n",
    "exp.events[\"perturbation\"] = event\n",
    "\n",
    "exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"V\"].equation.rhs = (\n",
    "    \"d*tau*((I + perturbation)*gamma - V**3*f + V**2*e + V*g \"\n",
    "    \"+ V*local_coupling + W*alpha + c_glob*gamma)\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "exp.integration.duration = T1\n",
    "exp.integration.step_size = DT\n",
    "\n",
    "res = exp.run()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "4c2eb70a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2160x1500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "res.integration.sel(variable=\"V\").plot(ax=ax)\n",
    "ax2 = ax.twinx()\n",
    "event.plot(ax=ax2, color=\"grey\")\n",
    "leg = ax2.get_legend()\n",
    "leg.set_loc('lower right')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ab98e75",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Run the same experiment again with a slower transmission speed. The edge lengths are unchanged; only `conduction_speed` changes, so delays scale as `length / conduction_speed`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "28953f40",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "STEP 1: Running simulation...\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "  Simulation period: 150.0 ms, dt: 0.2 ms\n",
      "  Transient period: 0.0 ms\n",
      "  Simulation complete.\n",
      "\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "Experiment complete.\n",
      "============================================================\n",
      "conduction_speed = 1 mm/ms\n",
      "[[  0.   0.   0.   0.   0.]\n",
      " [ 30.   0.   0.   0.   0.]\n",
      " [  0.  30.   0.   0.   0.]\n",
      " [100.   0.   0.   0.   0.]\n",
      " [  0.   0.   0.  30.   0.]]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2160x1500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "SLOW_CONDUCTION_SPEED = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "slow_network = Network.from_string(network_yaml)\n",
    "slow_network.parameters[\"conduction_speed\"].value = SLOW_CONDUCTION_SPEED\n",
    "\n",
    "slow_dynamics = Dynamics.from_db(\"Generic2dOscillator\")\n",
    "for name, value in DYNAMICS_PARAMS.items():\n",
    "    slow_dynamics.parameters[name].value = value\n",
    "\n",
    "slow_exp = SimulationExperiment(\n",
    "    dynamics=slow_dynamics,\n",
    "    coupling=Coupling(name=\"Linear\", parameters={\"a\": {\"value\": G_COUPLING}, \"b\": {\"value\": 0.0}}),\n",
    "    network=slow_network,\n",
    ")\n",
    "slow_exp.events[\"perturbation\"] = event\n",
    "slow_exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"V\"].equation.rhs = exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"V\"].equation.rhs\n",
    "slow_exp.integration.duration = T1\n",
    "slow_exp.integration.step_size = DT\n",
    "\n",
    "slow_res = slow_exp.run()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"conduction_speed = {SLOW_CONDUCTION_SPEED} mm/ms\")\n",
    "print(slow_network.calculate_delays())\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "slow_res.integration.sel(variable=\"V\").plot(ax=ax)\n",
    "ax2 = ax.twinx()\n",
    "event.plot(ax=ax2, color=\"grey\")\n",
    "leg = ax2.get_legend()\n",
    "leg.set_loc(\"lower right\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f05c547f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Result:** The current pulse starts at 10 ms and lasts 1 ms. R0's voltage peak appears later because the state variable needs time to move after the input turns on. Downstream peaks shift by `length / conduction_speed`: the 30 mm and 100 mm branches separate most clearly. The edges are directed, so the response does not travel back into earlier nodes.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Exercises\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Iso-energy comparison.** Keep the *energy* `amplitude × width` constant but shrink `width` (e.g. `width=20, amplitude=50` instead of `width=200, amplitude=5`). Plot the response. Is a brief, strong kick more or less efficient at triggering the limit cycle than a long, gentle one? Consider the system's relaxation time vs. the pulse duration.\n",
    "2. **Phase / timing effects.** Once the system is on the limit cycle, the response to a second pulse depends on **when** it arrives within the cycle. Re-run with two events (`exp.events[\"pulse1\"]`, `exp.events[\"pulse2\"]`) at the same amplitude but different `onset` values offset by a fraction of the cycle period. Compare the trajectories and look for constructive or destructive interference.\n",
    "3. **Sub-threshold pulse.** Reduce `amplitude` to `0.1` and re-run. You should see only a small damped twitch around the pulse, because the system never leaves the basin of the stable fixed point.\n",
    "4. **Closer to the bifurcation.** Set the baseline `I` (`exp.dynamics.parameters[\"I\"].value = 2.9`) and re-run with a small `amplitude`. A tiny perturbation now triggers oscillations.\n",
    "5. **Different waveform.** Replace the `Piecewise` rhs with a Gaussian, `amplitude*exp(-((t-onset)/width)**2)`, and observe the smoother response.\n",
    "6. **Different target.** Inject the event into `W` instead of `V` by editing `exp.dynamics.state_variables[\"W\"].equation.rhs`."
   ]
  }
 ],
